---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '../data/site-config';
---
<Layout
    title="Health Checks — Verify Your Ash-ISO Stack"
    description="Check that Qdrant, Ollama, LSFS daemon, and the launcher hook are all running correctly after deploying Ash-ISO."
    ogImage="/og-image.svg"
    ogUrl={`${SITE_CONFIG.siteUrl}/verify`}
>

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Health Checks — Verify Your Ash-ISO Stack</h1>
        <p class="lead">Every component in the semantic filesystem stack exposes a health endpoint or status command. Run these checks to confirm everything is working.</p>

        <section class="section" id="component-table">
            <h2>Component Health Overview</h2>
            <table class="health-table">
                <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Check</th><th>Expected</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Qdrant</td><td><code>curl :6333/health</code></td><td><code>{ "ok": true }</code></td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Ollama</td><td><code>curl :11434/api/tags</code></td><td>JSON with <code>nomic-embed-text</code> model</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>LSFS Daemon</td><td><code>systemctl --user status lsfs-daemon</code></td><td>Active (running)</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Launcher Hook</td><td><code>test -x /usr/local/bin/launch-lsfs.sh</code></td><td>Exit code 0</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="qdrant">
            <h2>1. Qdrant Vector Database</h2>
            <p>The semantic search backend. Runs in a Docker container on port <code>:6333</code>.</p>
            <pre><code>  curl -s http://localhost:6333/health
  # Expected: {"ok":true}</code></pre>
            <p>If Qdrant is not running: <code>sudo docker ps -a | grep qdrant</code> to see if the container exists, then <code>sudo docker start qdrant</code>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="ollama">
            <h2>2. Ollama LLM Runner</h2>
            <p>Runs the <code>nomic-embed-text</code> model for embeddings. Serves on port <code>:11434</code>.</p>
            <pre><code>  curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/tags
  # Expected: JSON object containing a "models" array with "nomic-embed-text:latest"</code></pre>
            <p>If the model is missing: <code>ollama pull nomic-embed-text</code>. If the service is down: <code>sudo systemctl restart ollama</code>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="lsfs">
            <h2>3. LSFS Semantic Daemon</h2>
            <p>The filesystem indexing daemon installed at <code>/opt/lsfs/</code>. Runs as a user service.</p>
            <pre><code>  systemctl --user status lsfs-daemon
  # Expected: ● lsfs-daemon.service - LSFS Semantic Filesystem Daemon
  #            Loaded: loaded
  #            Active: active (running)</code></pre>
            <p>If inactive: <code>systemctl --user enable --now lsfs-daemon</code>. Logs are in <code>~/.local/state/lsfs/</code>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="launcher">
            <h2>4. Rofi Launcher Hook</h2>
            <p>Bound to Super+Space in Hyprland. A simple shell script that wraps <code>rofi-lsfs</code>.</p>
            <pre><code>  test -x /usr/local/bin/launch-lsfs.sh && echo "Launcher OK"
  # Expected: Launcher OK</code></pre>
            <p>If missing: the install script should have placed it here. Re-run the one-liner to restore it.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="e2e">
            <h2>End-to-End Test</h2>
            <p>Verify the full pipeline — launcher, LSFS daemon, Ollama, and Qdrant — works together:</p>
            <pre><code>  # 1. Check LSFS indexes exist
  ls ~/.local/share/lsfs/indices/

  # 2. Query via the semantic launcher
  /usr/local/bin/launch-lsfs.sh "test query"

  # 3. Check Qdrant collection count
  curl -s http://localhost:6333/collections | jq '.result.collections | length'

  # All three should return data without errors.</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="fix-all">
            <h2>Fix-All</h2>
            <p>If any check fails, re-run the deploy script. It is fully idempotent and safe to run multiple times:</p>
            <pre><code>  curl -fsSL {SITE_CONFIG.deployUrl} | bash</code></pre>
            <p>This will re-install any missing components, restart services, and leave working configurations intact.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
  .health-table {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 800px;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 24px 0;
  }
  .health-table th, .health-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .health-table th {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }
  .health-table td {
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .health-table code {
    background: var(--bg-code);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 40px 0 16px;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .section p {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .section pre {
    background: var(--bg-code);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 20px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
</style>

</Layout>
